02:22.579 --> 02:25.315
BAEZ: <i> That's the car</i>
<i>we're looking for.</i>

02:32.436 --> 02:35.268
You guys ever heard of the DMV?
Huh?

02:35.270 --> 02:36.838
Your tag's expired.

02:36.840 --> 02:39.048
Turn off the ignition,

02:39.050 --> 02:41.786
put your keys and the hands
on the dashboard, both of you.

02:41.788 --> 02:43.451
Just write me a ticket, man.

02:43.453 --> 02:46.294
I got a better idea-- how about
you get your ass out of the car?

02:46.296 --> 02:48.159
You, too. Let's go.
DANNY: Come on.

02:48.161 --> 02:51.231
Come on, on
the sidewalk.

02:51.233 --> 02:54.032
Face the car.
Hands on the car.

02:54.034 --> 02:56.274
Anything in the trunk,
tough guy?

02:56.276 --> 02:58.178
Nah.
You mind if we take a look?

02:58.180 --> 02:59.210
You got a warrant?

02:59.212 --> 03:01.442
Don't need a warrant.

03:01.444 --> 03:03.178
What, are you a law
professor or something?

03:03.180 --> 03:05.019
Since when do you ask
all the questions?

03:07.422 --> 03:08.957
There's my warrant.

03:08.959 --> 03:10.726
(keyless lock beeping)

03:18.371 --> 03:20.802
Get on the ground.

03:20.804 --> 03:22.370
Get on the ground!
On the ground, on the ground!

03:22.372 --> 03:23.507
Turn around, get
on the ground now!

03:23.509 --> 03:25.243
Move!
Hands behind your head!

03:26.517 --> 03:27.977
Hands behind your
back. Let's go.

03:27.979 --> 03:29.513
I hope you got
a receipt for those.

03:29.515 --> 03:31.617
The judge will toss this out,
and we'll walk.

03:31.619 --> 03:33.217
You may walk, but you're
gonna have a tough time

03:33.219 --> 03:34.554
explaining how you lost

03:34.556 --> 03:36.354
$50,000 worth
of stolen hardware

03:36.356 --> 03:37.787
to your boss, aren't you?

03:37.789 --> 03:39.660
Now where's your law degree?

03:39.662 --> 03:41.534
Come on, get up.

03:50.408 --> 03:51.941
Hey, what are you
guys doing out here?

03:51.943 --> 03:54.213
Do me a favor-- take your hands
out of your pockets.

03:54.215 --> 03:56.277
Thanks a lot.
Why you hassling us?

03:56.279 --> 03:59.145
We've had multiple complaints
of drug activity on this block.

03:59.147 --> 04:00.881
You guys fit
the general description.

04:00.883 --> 04:01.977
Let me see your I.D.

04:01.979 --> 04:04.913
I want to see
all your I.D.'s.

04:08.323 --> 04:10.289
You got a weapon here?

04:11.123 --> 04:12.626
Man...

04:14.333 --> 04:17.798
What's this, your cold medicine?

04:20.168 --> 04:22.302
Hey, it's Curtis, Eddie.

04:25.009 --> 04:26.544
He got anything on him?

04:26.546 --> 04:28.449
No, he's clean.

04:28.451 --> 04:31.051
Curtis, come here.

04:31.053 --> 04:32.724
What are you doing
out here today, Curtis?

04:32.726 --> 04:34.621
I was just heading to work.

04:34.623 --> 04:35.989
Stopped to talk
for a minute,

04:35.991 --> 04:37.662
and then y'all show up.

04:37.664 --> 04:38.895
Your friends are wearing colors.

04:38.897 --> 04:40.857
What are you doing talking
to gangbangers, Curtis?

04:41.634 --> 04:43.106
They called me over.

04:43.108 --> 04:44.739
They run the neighborhood.

04:44.741 --> 04:46.781
I didn't want to disrespect 'em.

04:46.783 --> 04:48.078
All right, you still working
with your mother

04:48.080 --> 04:49.047
at St. Victor's Hospital?

04:49.049 --> 04:50.784
Yeah.
She talked

04:50.786 --> 04:52.888
to my sister-in-law-- she
asked me to check up on you.

04:52.890 --> 04:54.824
Said she's worried about you
hanging out with bad guys.

04:54.826 --> 04:57.191
Hey, I didn't
do anything wrong, so...

04:57.193 --> 04:59.390
Well, your friends,
they certainly did.

04:59.392 --> 05:02.694
Like I said,
they run the neighborhood.

05:02.696 --> 05:04.566
What else am I supposed to do?

05:04.568 --> 05:06.933
All right, you got a pass
this time, Curtis.

05:06.935 --> 05:09.101
But you got to watch the company
you keep, understand?

05:09.103 --> 05:11.437
Yeah.
All right.

05:11.439 --> 05:13.003
I'm late for work. Can I go?

05:13.005 --> 05:14.234
Yeah, take off.

05:16.339 --> 05:17.936
What do you think?

05:17.938 --> 05:19.272
I think he's a good kid.

05:19.274 --> 05:21.472
Hope it's enough
to keep him out of trouble.

05:24.180 --> 05:26.283
You've got the Brooklyn
borough president at 4:00,

05:26.285 --> 05:28.621
then cocktails
at Gracie Mansion.

05:28.623 --> 05:30.695
Five bucks if you get me
out of drinks with the mayor.

05:30.697 --> 05:33.360
Cost you way more than that.

05:48.980 --> 05:51.186
What is it?

06:19.279 --> 06:22.682
♪ ♪

06:51.650 --> 06:54.016
Get 'em back to work.
And, Sid...

06:55.754 --> 06:58.225
Everything we got.

